Subject: [PATCH 1/2] metal: force private VRAM allocation on discrete AMD GPUs

When llama.cpp's Metal backend runs on an Intel-Mac + AMD discrete GPU,
buffer allocations default to MTLStorageModeShared. On dedicated VRAM
hardware (Vega II / W6800X / RDNA1+2 discrete cards) this routes the
KV cache through PCIe-backed unified buffers, which serializes against
the CPU and makes the GPU's bandwidth advantage moot.

Force MTLStorageModePrivate for KV cache and weight tensors when the
active Metal device reports !isLowPower (i.e., the discrete GPU, not
the iGPU). Apple Silicon paths are unaffected because they take a
different code path before reaching the storage-mode decision.

